    "body": "### Problem\n\nKeycap Digit One Emoji \"1Ô∏è‚É£\" (U+0031, U+FE0F, U+20E3) is not property displayed.\nIt seems the characters has incorrect size.\nLayout is corrupted after page up/down or any edit.\nRefresh (`^L`) helps in most cases.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- run `nvim --clean`\n- insert mode (`i`), type `a`\n- insert `1Ô∏è‚É£` (shift + middle mouse button) ‚Äì¬†the character is visible, cursor is in the middle of the character\n- type `b` ‚Äì 1Ô∏è‚É£ disappears \n- type \" \" (space) and insert `1Ô∏è‚É£` ‚Äì the character is visible\n- escape and insert line above (`O`) ‚Äì the second character disappears\n- escape and refresh (`^L`) ‚Äì the second character is visible again \n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/504d904d-11f6-44fa-a986-aba347dd8dac\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDisplay correct layout.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-690+gc752016976\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim-tiny 9.1.1244\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian 13 (testing)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.41.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nnvim-linux-x86_64.tar.gz",
